<item>
            <title>[FLINK-35069] ContinuousProcessingTimeTrigger continuously registers timers in a loop at the end of the window</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-35069</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In our production environment, &#160;when TumblingEventTimeWindows and ContinuousProcessingTimeTrigger are used in combination within a WindowOperator, we observe a situation where the timers are continuously registered in a loop at the end of the window, leading to the job being perpetually stuck in timer processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13068064/13068064_image-2024-04-09-20-23-54-415.png&quot; height=&quot;205&quot; width=&quot;516&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue can be reproduced using the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/8e80ff889701ed1abbb5c15cd3943b254f1fb5cc/flink-streaming-java/src/test/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/runtime/operators/windowing/ContinuousProcessingTimeTriggerTest.java#L177&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;UT&lt;/a&gt; provided by the pr.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
